                                                                    11 1451     
******************************************************************  11 1451     
*                                                                *  11 1451     
* Temperatures = 283.6, 293.6, 300.0,                            *  11 1451     
*         323.6, 350.0, 373.6, 400.0,                            *  11 1451     
*         423.6, 450.0, 473.6, 500.0,                            *  11 1451     
*         523.6, 550.0, 573.6, 600.0 K, 623.6 K                  *  11 1451     
*                                                                *  11 1451     
* Extrapolated temperature = 650.0 K                             *  11 1451     
*                                                                *  11 1451     
* This evaluation is based on the CAB Model for heavy water[1]   *  11 1451     
* in a liquid state, T < T-crit(D2O) = 643.8 K. The file (MF7)   *  11 1451     
* was generated using NJOY 99.396[1] with a patch (upcab). One   *  11 1451     
* temperature point at 650 K was added for backward              *  11 1451     
* compatibility with ENDF/B-VII.1 scripts.                       *  11 1451     
*                                                                *  11 1451     
* The CAB model is a further development of ENDF/B-VII (2006)    *  11 1451     
* and IKE, Stuttgart (2005) models for heavy water (n + D2O);    *  11 1451     
* vibrational spectrum decomposition is applied. The continuous  *  11 1451     
* spectrum is based on MD GROMACS Calculations[2] and diffusion  *  11 1451     
* coefficients measured by Yoshida[3] and Mills[4].              *  11 1451     
*                                                                *  11 1451     
* For n + H-2-in-D2O, Skold approximation was applied for        *  11 1451     
* coherent inelastic correction with partial structure factors   *  11 1451     
* validated against experimental data measured by Soper[5].      *  11 1451     
* sig_coh(H-2)/sig_s(H-2) = 0.73194 .                            *  11 1451     
*                                                                *  11 1451     
* For oxygen in D2O, a new evaluation of the scattering kernel   *  11 1451     
* was prepared (free gas model is not applied). The scattering   *  11 1451     
* kernels for H-2-in-D2O and O-16-in-D2O were tested with        *  11 1451     
* criticality calculations in collaboration with D. Roubtsov     *  11 1451     
* from Canadian Nuclear Laboratories[6].                         *  11 1451     
*                                                                *  11 1451     
* The evaluation was prepared by:                                *  11 1451     
*                                                                *  11 1451     
* J.I. Marquez Damian, F. Cantargi, and J.R. Granada             *  11 1451     
* Nuclear Data Group - Neutron Physics Department                *  11 1451     
* Centro Atomico Bariloche - Argentina (CAB):                    *  11 1451     
*                                                                *  11 1451     
*  and                                                           *  11 1451     
*                                                                *  11 1451     
